sed violence (Human Rights Council 2008). The Sixth South Asia Ministerial Conference on \u201cCommemorating Beijing\u201d also recognized the importance of such concerted efforts (New", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "3566d55a-88c6-465e-89ea-a6ad7f6aecbd": {"__data__": {"id_": "3566d55a-88c6-465e-89ea-a6ad7f6aecbd", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/e-discussion-gender-overcoming-unequal-power-unequal-voice", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "E-Discussion: Gender \u2013 Overcoming Unequal Power, Unequal Voice", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/e-discussion-gender-overcoming-unequal-power-unequal-voice", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "7ea886a5ec6b92309a0295bfd964d6edeb7485f1720a6c4faa5e84c55ec5434b"}, "3": {"node_id": "097b6048-88ec-461e-8ff0-bb5c3fb7f2cb", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/e-discussion-gender-overcoming-unequal-power-unequal-voice", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "01aa4b537dbf517d847fc1b3548446a672a476174790b9fee31893cbdb3fc389"}}, "hash": "a1b1209e0aa7f698b2a42bd0a1e57fefbb58f7c1c72755c70272f61f104ae6c3", "text": "Delhi, 17-19 January 2008). Ministers, secretaries and senior government officers, women\u2019s groups/networks, civil society, and researchers from South Asia (Afghanistan, Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and 