l, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "20a24396-e4c5-4f6a-aa18-044a40f869fd": {"__data__": {"id_": "20a24396-e4c5-4f6a-aa18-044a40f869fd", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/estimating-sub-national-human-development-indices-presence-limited-information-case-bhutan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Estimating Sub-National Human Development Indices in the Presence of Limited Information: The Case of Bhutan", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/estimating-sub-national-human-development-indices-presence-limited-information-case-bhutan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "a748547d38cd25a02c28d5ab1f0266689f2b69708978d2fd4889c8d56675af4c"}, "2": {"node_id": "69e2ab3b-1261-45bd-a793-c4063c7e42d3", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/estimating-sub-national-human-development-indices-presence-limited-information-case-bhutan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "7c747969d6440a83fbfbfad7f998462ed93387c0371f87efc3d25a37e71d2f3e"}}, "hash": "6ed317c66e2da6c867650eb6cd3fc52bdbae2184021d89848481647db3e91b74", "text": "Besides India, other Asia-Pacific countries, including Cambodia and Indonesia, have produced sub- national HDRs and HDIs. Sub-national HDIs require more disaggregated data, which poses a huge challenge for the national accounts of many countries were not designed to collect such data. Further, indicators of health con- ditions, including deaths, at the sub-national level are often not available in many statistical systems. While proxy methods for generating the necessary data can always be found, it is crucially important that these alternative methods are robust and consistent. This paper attempts innovative ways to estimate sub-national level life expectancy at birth and per capita GDP for Bhutan in order to calculate sub-national HDIs. The estimates, produced for all 20 dzongkhags (provinces), show that human development in all dzongkhags is in the medium range", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "fb38f840-7fe8-4010-8746-e09e4b54e811": {"__data__": {"id_": "fb38f840-7fe8-4010-8746-e09e4b54e811", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/estimating-sub-national-human-development-indices-presence-limited-information-case-bhutan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Estimating Sub-National Human Development Indices in the Presence of Limited Information: The Case of Bhutan", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/estimating-sub-national-human-development-indices-presence-limited-information-case-bhutan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "36a53c29d3f8cd5e6e579dbb0e4ece9c355a364d2bebe87c4bef868dcc15c891"}, "3": {"node_id": "9840df09-e3e5-45b5-a3a2-b563d7ba55e2", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/estimating-sub-national-human-development-indices-presence-limited-information-case-bhutan", "Author": "