hat for calculating national HDIs, as noted previously. The same indicators are also required for both levels of calculations, but they are more disaggregated: for sub-national HDIs. Indeed, the latter require a disaggregated dataset for which the national accounts of many countries, especially the poorer ones, were not designed to collect, process and disseminate. Once there is clarity about the indicators for the three dimensions of HDI, the next step is to make the indicators scale-free or unit-free in order to make them additive and easy to per- form arithmetical operations on.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "86a32896-a475-4fdc-9901-df4b94ceafc0": {"__data__": {"id_": "86a32896-a475-4fdc-9901-df4b94ceafc0", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/estimating-sub-national-human-development-indices-presence-limited-information-case-bhutan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Estimating Sub-National Human Development Indices in the Presence of Limited Information: The Case of Bhutan", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/estimating-sub-national-human-development-indices-presence-limited-information-case-bhutan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "56a35da427b19f8b27e0db7903914d73a25c7157efd635fdca30247b927bf815"}, "2": {"node_id": "9d3cd9a9-1642-4475-9d5c-0abac914ce6f", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/estimating-sub-national-human-development-indices-presence-limited-i