ing session for the estimation of HDI for diverse stakeholders, especially those who will provide and use the estimates, including government officials, the media, academia, NGOs and donors. This will facili- tate a better understanding of human devel- opment and the HDI. It will also strengthen local capacity to estimate the HDI. 25 The Case of Bhutan References Alkire, Sabina, Maria Emma Santos, and Karma Ura. n.d. \u201cGross national happiness and pov- erty in Bhutan: Preliminary explorations using pilot data\u201d. [http://www.bhutanstudies.org.bt/admin/ pubFiles/13.GNH4.pdf]. Last accessed on 9 December 2009. BLSS (Bhutan Living Standard Survey). 2007. Bhutan living standard survey report. National Statistics Bureau. Thimphu: Royal Government of Bhutan. Brillinger, David R. 1986. \u201cThe natural variability of vital rates and associated statistics\u201d. Biometrics 42 (4): 693-734. Chiang, Chin Long. 1978. Life table and mortality analysis. Geneva: World Health Organization. Chiang, Chin Long. 1968. Introduction to stochastic processes in biostatistics. New York: John Wiley & Sons. Eayres, D., and E.S. Williams. 2004. \u201cEvaluation of methodologies for small area life expectancy estimation\u201d. Journal of Epidemiology and Community Health 58 (3): 243-249. Government of Madhya Pradesh. 2007. \u201cTechnical notes on the human development index\u201d. In Government of Madhya Pradesh. Madhya Pradesh human development report: Infrastructure for human development. New Delhi: Oxford University Press. Griffiths, Clare, and Justine Fitzpatrick. 2001. \u201cGeographic inequalities in life expectancy in the United Kingdom, 1995-97\u201d. Health Statistics Quarterly 9: 16-28. Haq, Mahbub Ul. 1995. Reflections on human development. New York: Oxford University Press. Limbu, Tara. 2009. \u201cHow war-distressed Sri Lanka beats Bhutan in HDI\u201d. Bhutan Times. June 14. Newell, Colin. 1994. Methods and models in demography. Chichester: John Wiley & Sons. Osmani, S.R.